title: Youth unemployment rate in Botswana in 2019
summary: In general Youth unemployment rate has fallen over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is slightly increasing from 2002 to 2003, gradually decreasing from 2003 to 2006, roughly constant from 2006 to 2008, slightly increasing from 2008 to 2010, and finally roughly constant from 2010 to 2012.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2003 and 2004.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 46.62 was reported at Year 2003
The lowest Youth unemployment rate, of value 30.77 was reported at Year 2008
